vior of D.\n**My vote:** Candidate\u202fA\nMETADATA_JSON:\n{\"agent\": \"agent_2\", \"vote\": \"Candidate A\"}", "thoughts": "We need to produce public message and metadata with vote. We have to evaluate candidates based on given attributes. Let's list attributes:\n\nCandidate A:\n- can anticipate dangerous situations. (positive)\n- able to see complex connections. (positive)\n- excellent spatial vision. (positive)\n- very good leadership qualities. (positive)\n- regarded as a show-off. (negative)\n- regarded as being not open to new ideas. (negative)\n\nCandidate B:\n- very conscientious. (positive)\n- handles stress very well. (positive)\n- good at assessing weather conditions. (positive)\n- excellent computer skills. (positive)\n- relatively weak memory for numbers. (negative)\n- makes nasty remarks about his colleagues. (negative)\n\nCandidate C:\n- can make correct decisions quickly. (positive)\n- difficulty communicating ideas. (negative)\n- regarded as egocentric. (negative)\n- not very willing to further his education. (negative)\n- keeps calm in a crisis. (positive)\n- understands complicated technology. (positive)\n\nCandidate D:\n- responds to unexpected events adequately. (positive)\n- can concentrate very well. (positive)\n- solves problems extremely well. (positive)\n- takes responsibility seriously. (positive)\n- regarded as a know-it-all. (negative)\n- has a hot temper. (negative)\n\nNow evaluate against criteria: reliability/responsibility, technical competence, calmness under pressure, decision-making, teamwork/communication, professional development.\n\nCandidate A: strong anticipation, complex connections, spatial vision, leadership => good technical and decision-making, reliability. Negatives: show-off, not open to new ideas => may affect teamwork, communication, professional development. Show-off could affect crew cooperation. Not open to new ideas could hinder learning. Overall strong but teamwork issues.\n\nCandidate B: conscientious, stress handling, weather assessment, computer skills => reliability, technical competence, calm under pressure. Negatives: weak memory for numbers (could affect navigation), nasty remarks about colleagues => teamwork problem. Memory issue could be serious for long-distance flights. Nasty remarks severe for crew cooperation.\n\nCandidate C: quick correct decisions, calm in crisis, understands tech => good decision-making, calm, technical competence. Negatives: communication difficulty, egocentric, unwilling to further education => teamwork and professional development issues. Egocentric may affect crew cooperation.\n\nCandidate D: responds adequately to unexpected events, concentration, problem solving, responsibility => reliability, technical competence, decision-making. Negatives: know-it-all, hot temper => teamwork issues, may affect crew under stress.\n\nAll have some teamwork issues. Which is least severe? Candidate D's hot temper could be serious under long flights. Candidate B's nasty remarks also severe. Candidate A's show-off maybe less severe? Not open to new ideas could affect adaptability. Candidate C's egocentric and communication difficulty also severe.\n\nWe need to weigh seriousness for safe long-distance flight. Technical competence and calmness are crucial. Teamwork also crucial. Which candidate balances? Candidate D has strong technical and responsibility, but hot temper and know-it-all may affect crew. Candidate A has strong anticipation and leadership, but not open to new ideas may affect adaptability to new procedures. Show-off maybe less impact. Candidate B has good stress handling and weather assessment, but weak memory for numbers could be dangerous for navigation. Candidate C has quick decisions and calm, but communication issues and unwillingness to learn.\n\nProbably Candidate D seems strongest technically and responsibility, but hot temper could be mitigated? However we cannot mitigate; we must weigh as evidence. Candidate A's not open to new ideas could affect long-term suitability. Candidate B's memory issue is serious. Candidate C's communication issues also serious.\n\nThus maybe Candidate D is best despite temper, because technical and responsibility are top, and temperament may be less fatal than memory issues. But hot temper could cause conflict under stress. Which is more severe? Memory for numbers could cause navigation errors. Show-off may be less severe. Not open to new ideas may affect learning but not immediate safety. Hot temper could cause poor decisions under pressure. However D also \"responds to unexpected events adequately\" not outstanding but okay.\n\nI think Candidate A might be best: strong anticipation, spatial vision, leadership, ability to see complex connections (good for long flights). Teamwork issues: show-off, not open to new ideas. Those could be managed. No mention of memory issues or hot temper. So overall safety maybe higher.\n\nThus I will vote Candidate A.\n\nNow produce public message summarizing reasoning and vote."}
