th concerns. For long-haul, health (eating) could affect performance. Unfriendly and show-off could affect crew. Not open to new ideas could affect adaptation to new tech/regulations.\n\nCandidate B: conscientious, stress handling, weather assessment, computer skills. Weak memory for numbers (critical), nasty remarks, uncooperative, pretentious. Those are serious for teamwork and navigation.\n\nCandidate C: 100% reliable, positive crew atmosphere, quick correct decisions, calm, understands tech, excellent attention, puts concern for others above everything. Negatives: difficulty communicating ideas, egocentric, not willing to further education. Communication difficulty could affect crew coordination, egocentric could affect teamwork. Not willing to further education could affect long-term suitability.\n\nCandidate D: takes responsibility, concentration, problem solving, responds adequately, but moody, loner, arrogant, weak leadership, hot temper. Those are serious for crew dynamics.\n\nOverall, C seems strongest overall: reliability, crew positive atmosphere, calm, decision-making, technical understanding. The communication difficulty is a concern but maybe mitigated by positive atmosphere and concern for others. Egocentric and unwillingness to further education are concerns for long-term development but not immediate safety.\n\nThus I would vote Candidate C.\n\nWe should also maybe ask other agents if they have any additional positive attributes for Candidate D or B that we might be missing, but we have all. Could ask about any additional strengths for Candidate A? But we have all. So maybe no need.\n\nWe can also note that we have considered all candidates and explain reasoning.\n\nThus produce PUBLIC_MESSAGE summarizing reasoning and vote.\n\nMETADATA_JSON with vote \"Candidate C\"."}
