r, know\u2011it\u2011all (from SMM). Also \"moody, loner\" etc.\n\nNow we need to decide best candidate for long-distance pilot. Criteria: reliability, technical competence, calmness, decision-making, teamwork/communication, professional development.\n\nLet's weigh each:\n\nReliability: C (100% reliable), D (takes responsibility seriously), B (very conscientious), A (no explicit reliability but leadership). So C highest.\n\nTechnical competence: A (anticipates danger, complex connections, spatial vision), B (weather assessment, computer), C (understands tech), D (problem solving, concentration). All decent. A maybe strongest for navigation.\n\nCalmness under pressure: B handles stress well, C keeps calm in crisis, D responds adequately, A not mentioned.\n\nDecision-making: A anticipates, sees connections; C makes correct decisions quickly; D solves problems extremely well; B not explicit.\n\nTeamwork/communication: C creates positive atmosphere, but difficulty communicating ideas, egocentric. A good leadership but show\u2011off, not open to ideas, unorganized, not good at criticism. B grumpy, uncooperative, nasty remarks. D weak leadership, arrogant, hot temper, moody.\n\nProfessional development: A not open to new ideas, B maybe okay, C not willing to further education, D not mentioned.\n\nThus trade-offs: C has reliability and positive crew atmosphere, but communication difficulty and egocentric may affect teamwork. However positive atmosphere may offset. D has strong problem solving and responsibility but temperament issues severe. B has memory weakness critical for navigation. A has strong technical but poor teamwork and health.\n\nThus C seems best overall. So we keep vote for C.\n\nWe should also maybe ask other agents if they have any additional positive attributes for candidate B or A? But we have all. Could ask about any additional positive attributes for candidate A? But we have all. The tool can be used to ask other agents about strengths we don't have. We have all strengths for each candidate. So no need.\n\nWe can contribute reasoning and reaffirm vote for C, maybe ask about severity of communication difficulty for C? But that's a weakness, not allowed. So we just share reasoning.\n\nThus produce public message summarizing evaluation and vote C."}
