e D positives: responds to unexpected events adequately, can concentrate very well, solves problems extremely well, takes responsibility seriously. That's all.\n\nThus no missing strengths. So we cannot ask for more.\n\nNow we need to produce public message: share reasoning, maybe adjust vote. Agent_2 previously voted Candidate A. Now after seeing others' arguments, we may reconsider. We need to evaluate again. Let's weigh.\n\nCandidate A: strong technical, leadership, but interpersonal issues (show-off, not open to new ideas, unorganized, not good at criticism, unhealthy eating). Those could affect crew and long-haul endurance. Not open to new ideas could affect professional development.\n\nCandidate B: good stress handling, conscientious, weather, computer, but weak memory for numbers (critical) and nasty remarks, uncooperative.\n\nCandidate C: reliability, positive crew atmosphere, quick correct decisions, calm, tech understanding, but communication difficulty, egocentric, unwilling to further education.\n\nCandidate D: responsibility, concentration, problem solving, adequate response, but arrogance, weak leadership, hot temper, know-it-all.\n\nWhich is best? Agent 2 originally favored A due to strong technical and leadership, thinking interpersonal issues less safety-critical. But after seeing others' arguments, maybe reconsider. The key for long-distance flights: reliability, crew coordination, decision-making, technical competence, calmness, and ability to adapt. Candidate C's reliability and positive crew atmosphere are strong for crew coordination. Communication difficulty is a concern but maybe mitigated by positive atmosphere? Egocentric may affect teamwork. Unwillingness to further education may affect long-term.\n\nCandidate A's technical strengths are high, but leadership is good but show-off and not open to ideas could hinder crew. Unorganized could affect flight planning. Health issues (unhealthy eating) could affect stamina.\n\nCandidate B's memory issue is serious for navigation. Interpersonal issues also.\n\nCandidate D's hot temper and arrogance could be dangerous under stress.\n\nThus C seems best overall. Agent 2 may change vote to C. But we need to consider if any new evidence could change. We could ask other agents if they have any additional positive attributes for candidate A or D that we missed. But we have all. Could ask about any positive attributes for candidate B? Already have all. So maybe we just update vote to C, providing reasoning.\n\nWe should also note open questions: severity of communication difficulty for C, etc. But we cannot ask about weaknesses. We can ask about strengths we might be missing. None.\n\nThus produce public message summarizing evaluation and vote for Candidate C.\n\nMETADATA_JSON with vote \"Candidate C\"."}
